    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
