        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the Wellington is in the oven, cut a large<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) approx. the size of a sheet of A3 paper</p><p>Lay the<strong> shredded kale</strong> in the middle with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and scrunch the edges of the foil around the shredded kale to form a sealed parcel[s] then place on a separate baking tray</p><p>Add the tray to the oven for 10-15 min or until tender – this is your <strong>roasted kale</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
